<br>
Focus items promise to be to casters what weapons and haste items are to melee, a way to boost their power and effectiveness in a way that’s been lacking since release. Seams like the easiest way to get focus items at first will be mag summons so they will have the most direct access to them. <br>
<br>
This is a very valid topic for a rogue board imo. If you remember back to pre-kunak mag and rogue were almost synonymous in a group. If you wanted good damage you could invite either one. Now these present focus items won’t put mages on par with rogue damage the way they should be but the better drop ones might. Rogues might find their unjust position as the ultimate damage dealer challenged at last.<br>
<br>
Mysthyl Endowyn<br>
Sorcerer of Drinal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uferessa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feressa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 9:11:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22859.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: you forgot</span><hr size=1> I very much doubt that Verant has tested these properly, and they've always had problems with getting caster balance right anyway. No-one in their right mind is going to pretend it's hard to level up to 50: Kunark made that process pretty easy. Does Verant really think that making the low levels a cake-walk is going to boost their subscriber base?<br>
