mino axe to the amount of damage a caster in the teens can produce...). The point at which they really start to need compensatory inflation is in the late 30's/early 40's, but fair enough, that isn't really a discussion for this forum.<br>
<br>
What really worries me is that this change will affect <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> all</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> spell-casting, in ways which I'm sure Verant hasn't tested (spell-casting haste is one area which might upset things severely). Verant seems to have discarded the notion that a challenging game is a fun game. Ok, sure, they often took that idea too far, but the core principle is still valid. There is progressively less challenge left in this game, what challenge is left consists mostly of either 'kill the mob before another group gets to it' or 'avoid the idiots who'll mess up and train you'. Some degree of mudflation is inevitable, but I really think they need to examine their decisions more closely before rushing out massive changes like these focus items.<br>
<br>
My main character is an enchanter, if I just wanted cheese, I should be dancing for joy. As it is, I can pump out 5.5k dpm in the right zones while watching TV. But frankly, I have the sneaking suspicion that I had more fun being wasted by frogs at the pyramid... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uravenwingedangel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenwinged Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 1:49:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22859.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> These arent gonna be real useful to high levels I'm afraid.<br>
