<br>
If I can't find a group one day, I solo light blues and hope not to die...If a mage can't find a group, they just say &quot;Oh, well&quot;, summon a pet, and go solo some nice blues with little risk if they do it right.<br>
<br>
If I want to get out of a zone, I hope that someone can port me...If a mage wants to get out of a zone, they just say &quot;Oh, well&quot;, and gate.<br>
<br>
I could go on and on, but what would be the point?  I had a mage (and good friend) tell me last night that mage pets should outdamage every class in the game besides rogues, and should be close to rogues.  So...if a mage with a pet outdamages every class in the game, or even comes close to melee damage classes...well, then what is the point of having any of the other classes, barring places with pathing concerns?  It should go without saying, but I guess it needs said again because apparently some people just don't get it...<br>
<br>
Casters get spells.  They get spells that do lots of damage fast.  Wizards get TL's and ports.  All casters can gate and bind.  With the right gear, int casters can solo almost as efficiently as they can group.  Rogues get...damage and stealth.  So if you put caster damage on par with rogue damage, then you're damaging the rogue class in comparison.  And make no mistake - people DO make those comparisons.  I don't parse logs, so I can't say where damage currently falls.  I'll just say that if ANY pet can outdamage a rogue, ranger, warrior, shadow knight, or paladin, and keep agro off of casters at the same time, then I feel that there's something seriously wrong.  For many classes, taking hits and dealing damage is the biggest part of their class.  They can't gate, they can't bind, and they can't nuke.  If you have a class that can do all those things AND has a pet on par with those other classes...well, in my mind that is NOT good for balance. <p><p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=37752">Darkrok Shadowwalker</a> - Redeemed <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/item.asp?Id=1926">Epicfied</a> Dwarven Rogue of <img src="http://www.templeofdawneq.com/templeofdawn/pictures/darkrok-level.gif"> Missions
